
[1]hopeful

   HO'PEFUL, a. Having qualities which excite hope; promising or giving
   ground to expect good or success; as a hopeful youth; a hopeful
   prospect.

   1. Full of hope or desire,with expectation.

   I was hopeful the success of your first attempts would encourage you to
   the trial of more nice and difficult experiments.
